                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7250</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-22T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 22, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reports from Los Mochis state that garrisons there and in Fuerte Valley are
                    inadequate to guard against possible incursion of Villistas from Chihuahua.
                    Request Foreign Office to have adequate protection given settlers Los Mochis
                    district, who have already suffered many hardships from raids by Indians and
                    Villistas.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
